For anyone that’s using either the stock PhotonVision implementation for RKNN object detection, or our high-FPS implementation, here are some flexible and documented jupyter notebooks to help you train YOLOv5 and YOLOv8 models to use with them (or with your own solution).
There are highly parametric and can be used for a bunch of use cases.

For the unfamiliar - Kaggle gives you 30 hours of GPU per week, which is plenty, offers better hardware than Google Colab, and lets you run notebooks in the background for 12 hours while you’re offline.

  • YOLOv5
  • YOLOv8
